name: OpenClaw
description: Open-source AI agent orchestration platform with native support for multi-agent workflows and tool routing.
fullDescription: OpenClaw is an open-source platform for building, deploying, and orchestrating AI agents at scale. With built-in support for multi-agent workflows, tool routing, and real-time monitoring, OpenClaw makes it easy to build production-ready agent systems.

name: Supabase
description: Open-source Firebase alternative with PostgreSQL database, authentication, and real-time subscriptions for agent data storage.
fullDescription: Supabase provides an open-source backend-as-a-service platform built on PostgreSQL. Perfect for storing agent conversation history, user data, and application state with built-in authentication and real-time capabilities.

name: Vercel
description: Deploy AI agents and web applications instantly with zero-config deployments and edge functions.
fullDescription: Vercel is the platform for frontend developers, providing the best experience for deploying modern web applications. Deploy your AI agent interfaces with automatic CI/CD, edge functions, and global CDN distribution.
integrationGuide:
# Install Vercel CLI
npm install -g vercel

# Deploy your agent app
vercel deploy

# Set environment variables
vercel env add OPENAI_API_KEY
vercel env add AGENT_CONFIG

# Deploy to production
vercel --prod

name: Anthropic
description: Build agents with Claude, the AI assistant known for safety, reliability, and extended context windows.
fullDescription: Anthropic's Claude models power intelligent, safe, and reliable AI agents. With support for 200K+ token context windows, function calling, and vision capabilities, Claude is ideal for complex agentic workflows.
features: Native function calling and tool use
Constitutional AI for safety and alignment

name: OpenAI
description: Power your agents with GPT-4 and advanced function calling capabilities for complex reasoning tasks.
fullDescription: OpenAI provides cutting-edge language models including GPT-4, GPT-4 Turbo, and GPT-4o. With advanced function calling, vision, and code interpreter capabilities, OpenAI models excel at complex agentic workflows.

name: Stripe
description: Accept payments and manage subscriptions for your agent services with developer-friendly APIs.
fullDescription: Stripe is the leading payment infrastructure for the internet. Enable your AI agents to process payments, manage subscriptions, and handle billing with a complete suite of payment APIs.

name: GitHub
description: Enable agents to interact with code repositories, issues, and pull requests via the GitHub API.
fullDescription: GitHub provides a comprehensive API for automating code workflows. Build agents that can review pull requests, manage issues, deploy code, and collaborate with your development team.

name: Cloudflare
description: Deploy agents globally on Cloudflare Workers with edge computing and built-in AI capabilities.
fullDescription: Cloudflare Workers enable you to deploy serverless AI agents at the edge, closer to your users. With built-in AI models via Workers AI and vector storage via Vectorize, build low-latency agent experiences.

name: LangChain
description: Build complex agent chains and workflows with the leading framework for LLM application development.
fullDescription: LangChain is the most popular framework for building applications with large language models. Create sophisticated agent workflows with built-in memory, tools, and chain orchestration.

name: CrewAI
description: Orchestrate multi-agent teams where specialized agents collaborate to complete complex tasks.
fullDescription: CrewAI enables you to create teams of AI agents that work together, each with their own role, goal, and backstory. Build collaborative agent systems that divide and conquer complex problems.
integrationGuide:
pip install crewai

from crewai import Agent, Task, Crew

researcher = Agent(
  role='Researcher',
  goal='Research AI agent frameworks',
  backstory='Expert AI researcher'
)

writer = Agent(
  role='Writer',
  goal='Write technical documentation',
  backstory='Technical writer with 10 years exp'
)

task = Task(
  description='Research and write about agents',
  agent=researcher
)

crew = Crew(agents=[researcher, writer], tasks=[task])
result = crew.kickoff()

name: AutoGPT
description: Open-source autonomous agent framework that can self-direct to achieve complex goals with minimal guidance.
fullDescription: AutoGPT is one of the pioneering autonomous agent frameworks that can break down goals, execute tasks, and iterate on solutions with minimal human intervention. Build self-directed agents that can research, code, and problem-solve.
integrationGuide:
pip install autogpt

from autogpt.agent import Agent
from autogpt.config import Config

config = Config()
agent = Agent(
  ai_name='ResearchBot',
  memory=Memory(),
  config=config
)

result = agent.start_interaction_loop(
  goal='Research the latest AI agent frameworks'
)

name: Composio
description: Connect your agents to 150+ tools and APIs with a unified interface for seamless integration.
fullDescription: Composio provides a universal API gateway for connecting AI agents to popular tools and services. From calendar management to CRM integrations, give your agents the tools they need through a single, consistent interface.
